regions.title: Shoulder and upper torso region
regions.description: This region covers both shoulders and the upper chest, spanning across the full width of the highlighted area, which is consistent with the expected position of shoulders in a frontal portrait.

summary: Most identified cells correspond well to the expected location of shoulders in the image, forming a broad, connected band across the upper torso. Central cells with lower confidence and less visual alignment to the shoulders were removed for accuracy.
